<HEADLINE>
TAITRA TO HOLD ICT INDUSTRY FORUM AT HANOVER CEBIT SHOW
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Feb.  15 (CNA) 02/15/07  20:02:31 (By Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Taiwan External Trade Development Council
(TAITRA) will hold a forum on the development of the information
and communications technology (ICT) industry at the upcoming 2007
CeBIT show in Hanover, Germany, TAITRA officials said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan ICT industry forum is slated for March 16, with
representatives of the German Association for Information
Technology, Telecommunications and New Media, O2 -- a leading
European company in telecommunications operations, and major
mobile phone manufacturers of Taiwan invited to attend for talks
about the ICT industry's future development, according to TAITRA
officials.
</P>
<P>
CeBIT, the world's largest trade fair showcasing digital IT and
telecommunications solutions, will be held March 15-21 with the
participation of more than 6,000 businesses from 71 countries.
Over 570 of the participants will be from Taiwan, the officials
said.
</P>
<P>
Displays at the fair's 24 exhibition halls will be divided into
six major sections -- business processes, communications, digital
equipment and systems, banking and finance, the public sector,
and the future. The event is expected to draw around 450,000
visitors from around the world.
</P>
<P>
Over 6,200 exhibitors from around 70 countries and some 430,000
visitors attended the 2006 CeBIT show.
</P>
